## Key Issues and Challenges

| Issue                          | Electoral College System                      | Direct Popular Vote System                      |
|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Vote Weight                   | Unequal; small states overrepresented        | Equal; one person, one vote                      |
| Campaign Focus               | Swing states dominate                         | Nationwide campaign focus                        |
| Minority Interests           | Protected via state-based electors            | Risk of marginalization of rural/minority areas |
| Election Outcome             | Possible to win without popular vote majority | Winner always has popular vote majority         |
| Recount Complexity           | Limited to few states                         | Potentially nationwide                           |
| Political Stability          | Two-party system reinforced                   | Risk of multi-party fragmentation               |
| Constitutional Change Needed | No                                           | Yes                                             |

