## Alternatives and Reform Proposals

- **National Popular Vote Interstate Compact (NPVIC):** An agreement among states to award their electors to the national popular vote winner once states totaling 270 electoral votes join. Currently, 16 states plus DC with 196 votes have joined, short of the 270 threshold ([Abolish the Electoral College PAC, 2019](https://abolishtheelectoralcollegepac.org)).

- **Proportional Allocation:** Electoral votes distributed proportionally based on state popular vote.

- **District Plan:** Electoral votes allocated by congressional district, as done partially by Maine and Nebraska.

These reforms aim to mitigate Electoral College issues without full abolition but face legal and political hurdles ([Brennan Center, 2019](https://www.brennancenter.org/our-work/research-reports/electoral-college-reform)).

